<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-02-26T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-02-26T17:00:00-05:00" n="557" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d557">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">881.044/30: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Chargé at Tangier</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Childs</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-02-26T18:00:00-04:00">February 26, 1944—6 p.m.</date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>27. The Department approves, reference your airgram A–25, February 8,
                                6 p.m., extension of the requisition measures to olive crops of
                                American <hi rend="italic">ressortissants</hi> in French Morocco
                                subject to the reservations outlined in your airgram. In this
                                connection see Algiers telegram no. 490, February 15, 8 p.m. to the
                                Department.</p>
                            <p>Repeat to Algiers, Casablanca and Rabat.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Stettinius</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>